{"from": {"id": "100000182091980", "name": "Ljubomir Ljubojevi\u0107"}, "revision": "10152734103297728", "updated_time": "2014-09-04T17:41:05+0000", "created_time": "2014-09-04T17:37:42+0000", "message": "<p><b><u>Note:</u></b> This is SAMBA config I used on one server. I am posting it here because it works for sure, so you can test your own servers when in doubt.<br /><b><u>Note: </u></b>I do not wouch that these settings are good, secure, etc., all I am saying is that it works in protected network.<br /><b><u>Note: </u></b>You can modify only most necessary items and test if it works for you. When you see it works, then change one setting at the time, restart samba, check, and if it works change another setting.<br /><br />[global]<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 log file = /var/log/samba/log.%m<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 netbios name = server<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 guest account = nobody<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 netbios aliases = linux<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 writeable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 server string = Server<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 log level = audit:3<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 sync always = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 workgroup = VODOREMONT<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 guest ok = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 os level = 20<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 auto services = global homes printers<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 username map = /etc/samba/smbusers<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 encrypt passwords = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 security = share<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 passdb backend = tdbsam<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 max log size = 50<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 wins support = true<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 allow hosts = 192.168.1.0/24<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 cups options = raw<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 load printers = yes<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 restrict anonymous = 0<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 null passwords = no<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 ----------<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 -----------<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 username map = /etc/samba/smbusers<br /><br /><br />[homes]<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 comment = Home Directories<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 browseable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 writable = yes<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 valid users = %S<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 valid users = MYDOMAIN\\%S<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <br />[printers]<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 comment = All Printers<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 path = /var/spool/samba<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 browseable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 guest ok = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 writable = no<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 printable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <br />[d-disk]<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 browseable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 guest ok = yes<br />;\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 guest account = tanja<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 writeable = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 delete readonly = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 public = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 path = /extra<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 sync always = yes<br />\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 read only = no<br /></p><br /><br />", "subject": "Working samba config", "id": "10152734097672728", "icon": "https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/y7/r/8zhNI-VGpiI.png"}